==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insession
<hw>In*ses"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insessio</ets>, fr. <ets>insidere</ets>, <ets>insessum</ets>, to
sit in. See <er>Insidious</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of sitting, as in a tub or bath.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Used by way of fomentation, <xex>insession</xex>, or bath.⟦rdquo⟧
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That in which one sits, as a bathing tub.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Insessions</qex> be bathing tubs half full.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insessor</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
